## ğŸ”¹ 1. shape

### ğŸ“Œ What it does
`shape` returns a **tuple representing the dimensions** of a NumPy array.

- For 2D arrays â†’ `(rows, columns)`
- For 1D arrays â†’ `(elements,)`

### âœ… Syntax
```python
array.shape
âœ… Example
python
Copy code
import numpy as np

arr = np.array([[1, 2, 3],
                [4, 5, 6]])

print(arr.shape)
ğŸ”¸ Output
text
Copy code
(2, 3)
ğŸ“Œ Meaning
2 â†’ number of rows

3 â†’ number of columns

ğŸ”¹ 2. ndim
ğŸ“Œ What it does
ndim returns the number of dimensions (axes) of an array.

âœ… Example
python
Copy code
import numpy as np

a = np.array(10)
b = np.array([1, 2, 3])
c = np.array([[1, 2], [3, 4]])

print(a.ndim)
print(b.ndim)
print(c.ndim)
ğŸ”¸ Output
text
Copy code
0
1
2
ğŸ“Œ Explanation
Scalar â†’ 0D

1D Array (Vector) â†’ 1D

2D Array (Matrix) â†’ 2D

ğŸ”¹ 3. ndmin
ğŸ“Œ What it does
ndmin forces an array to have a minimum number of dimensions, even if the data is small.

âœ… Example
python
Copy code
import numpy as np

arr = np.array([1, 2, 3], ndmin=3)

print(arr)
print(arr.ndim)
ğŸ”¸ Output
text
Copy code
[[[1 2 3]]]
3
ğŸ“Œ Why this happens
Original array is 1D

ndmin=3 adds extra dimensions from the left

ğŸ“Œ Use case
Required when ML models or APIs expect fixed dimensions

Useful in deep learning (CNNs, RNNs)

ğŸ”¹ 4. reshape()
ğŸ“Œ What it does
reshape() changes the shape of an array without modifying the data.

âœ… Syntax
python
Copy code
array.reshape(rows, columns)
âœ… Example
python
Copy code
import numpy as np

arr = np.array([1, 2, 3, 4, 5, 6])

reshaped = arr.reshape(2, 3)
print(reshaped)
ğŸ”¸ Output
text
Copy code
[[1 2 3]
 [4 5 6]]
ğŸ“Œ Important Rule
pgsql
Copy code
rows Ã— columns = total elements
If the rule is violated â†’ âŒ Error occurs.

ğŸ”¹ 5. -1 Concept (Auto Dimension)
ğŸ“Œ What it does
Using -1 allows NumPy to automatically calculate the missing dimension.

âœ… Example (Columns auto)
python
Copy code
import numpy as np

arr = np.array([1, 2, 3, 4, 5, 6])

new_arr = arr.reshape(2, -1)
print(new_arr)
print(new_arr.shape)
ğŸ”¸ Output
text
Copy code
[[1 2 3]
 [4 5 6]]
(2, 3)
ğŸ“Œ Explanation
Total elements = 6

Rows fixed = 2

Columns calculated automatically = 3

âœ… Example (Rows auto)
python
Copy code
import numpy as np

arr = np.array([1, 2, 3, 4, 5, 6])

new_arr = arr.reshape(-1, 2)
print(new_arr)
ğŸ”¸ Output
text
Copy code
[[1 2]
 [3 4]
 [5 6]]
âš ï¸ Important Notes
Only one -1 is allowed in reshape()

NumPy cannot guess multiple unknown dimensions

ğŸ§  Interview Notes (Very Important)
Concept	Meaning
shape	Returns array dimensions
ndim	Number of dimensions
ndmin	Forces minimum dimensions
reshape	Changes array shape
-1	Auto-calculates dimension

ğŸ’¡ Real-World Applications
Machine Learning model input formatting

Image reshaping (pixels â†’ matrix)

Data preprocessing before training

Converting 1D data into tabular format

âœ… Summary
shape â†’ size of array

ndim â†’ number of dimensions

ndmin â†’ force dimensions

reshape() â†’ change layout

-1 â†’ automatic dimension handling

