# ğŸ“˜ NumPy Day 3 â€“ Shape, ndim & Reshape (Simple Notes)

---

## ğŸ”¹ shape
### Definition  
`shape` shows the size of the array (rows, columns).

### Example
```python
import numpy as np

arr = np.array([[1, 2, 3],
                [4, 5, 6]])

print(arr.shape)
Output
text
Copy code
(2, 3)
ğŸ‘‰ 2 rows and 3 columns

ğŸ”¹ ndim
Definition
ndim tells how many dimensions an array has.

Example
python
Copy code
import numpy as np

a = np.array(10)
b = np.array([1, 2, 3])
c = np.array([[1, 2], [3, 4]])

print(a.ndim)
print(b.ndim)
print(c.ndim)
Output
text
Copy code
0
1
2
ğŸ‘‰
0D = number
1D = list
2D = table (matrix)

ğŸ”¹ ndmin
Definition
ndmin forces an array to have minimum number of dimensions.

Example
python
Copy code
import numpy as np

arr = np.array([1, 2, 3], ndmin=3)

print(arr)
print(arr.ndim)
Output
text
Copy code
[[[1 2 3]]]
3
ğŸ‘‰ Array is forced into 3 dimensions

ğŸ”¹ reshape()
Definition
reshape() changes the shape of the array without changing data.

Example
python
Copy code
import numpy as np

arr = np.array([1, 2, 3, 4, 5, 6])

print(arr.reshape(2, 3))
Output
text
Copy code
[[1 2 3]
 [4 5 6]]
ğŸ‘‰ Rule: rows Ã— columns = total elements

ğŸ”¹ -1 (Auto Dimension)
Definition
-1 lets NumPy automatically calculate the missing size.

Example
python
Copy code
import numpy as np

arr = np.array([1, 2, 3, 4, 5, 6])

print(arr.reshape(2, -1))
Output
text
Copy code
[[1 2 3]
 [4 5 6]]
ğŸ‘‰ NumPy decides the column size

Another Example
python
Copy code
print(arr.reshape(-1, 2))
Output
text
Copy code
[[1 2]
 [3 4]
 [5 6]]
ğŸ§  Quick Summary
Concept	Simple Meaning
shape	Size of array
ndim	Number of dimensions
ndmin	Force dimensions
reshape	Change array shape
-1	Auto size

ğŸ’¡ Uses
Machine learning input format

Image reshaping

Data preprocessing
